<img src="https://biz-file.com/c/1908/512012-625x325.jpg" alt="Image source: Gallo/Getty." width="625" height="325">Image source: Gallo/Getty.BABA TV is available on the DStv platform on channel 374. The managing director of BABA TV, Moses Grace Balyeku, declared, “We believe that DStv viewers will be happy to see the inclusion of another local content channel, and it gives us as Basoga great pride in knowing that we have reached the calibRe of content that is DStv-worthy.The managing director of MultiChoice Uganda, Hassan Saleh, said, “As we continue to look out for local content that is of great quality, it is always refreshing to land on channels like BABA TV through which we can give viewers what they have interest in.”The speaker of Parliament, Rebecca Kadaga, who was present on the launch encouraged the team from BABA TV on reaching this milestone.Kadaga further stated, ‘’We should all work towards showing the best possible news and content to attract partnerships like the one we see taking effect here today between DStv and BABA TV.’’